race.comment: FOSSE (7) has been close up in all 3 starts this prep at Ellerslie, and rocketed home late there 18 days ago when finishing fourth. The step up to a middle distance is the key, and she is the one to beat. KWANZA (3) battled away bravely for fourth over 2400m at Te Rapa nearly 4 weeks ago. The side winkers go on, and he should be right in the finish this time. Each way value. BRUNO (18) ran a much better race here last time out, finishing fourth. He gets a nice swing in his draw this time, and can break his long run of outs here. Include in all combinations. MADAM PELE (20) is very hard to catch, but meets the right sort of field here, and could be one to spice up any top 4 combos. ALTEZZA (12) was doing her best work late over 1400m 3 weeks ago at Tauherenikau, and will relish the quick step up to a middle distance here. His only win came on this track, and she is not to be taken lightly. COTTON ROCA (5) stepped up in trip and found winning form here 17 days ago. Stick with her.
